An acupuncturist shall maintain a record for each patient treated, in a manner consistent with the acceptable and prevailing standards of practice within the Commonwealth. At a minimum, the record for each patient shall include:
A signed copy of the information disclosed by the acupuncturist to the patient under KRS 311.678;
Evidence that the acupuncturist has conducted or overseen an interview concerning the patient's medical history and current physical condition;
Evidence of the acupuncturist having conducted a traditional acupuncture examination;
A record of the treatment, including the acupuncture points treated; and
The evaluation and instructions given.
